23/11/2010
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Incumbent Republika Srpska (RS) Finance Minister Aleksandar Dzombic has been nominated by the Alliance of Independent Social Democrats (SNSD) to serve as the entity's new prime minister, following the October 3rd general elections.
He was the unanimous choice of the main board of RS's largest party in a vote Monday (November 22nd).
Dzombic must next be formally appointed by RS President Milorad Dodik, and then starts consultations to form his government.
When he is ready with his cabinet picks, the president forwards the line-up to parliament, which will have 40 days to confirm it.
(RTRS, RTS, Nezavisne Novine, BHRT - 22/11/10)
